Rating: 3
It's only cornbread, so I couldn't give it 4 forks, but it is tasty and easy. I used about 2 cups frozen blueberries instead of raspberries, used cornmeal because I like the grittiness, and baked it all in a buttered cast iron skillet to give it a nice crust. This all worked out great, but required about a 30 minute baking time. My boyfriend, who claims to not like cornbread, said it was the best cornbread ever and concluded that he's never actually had good cornbread before this.

Rating: 3
I whipped up a batch of these muffins this afternoon in an effort to use up my fresh raspberries. I baked the entire batch in a 9-inch cast iron skillet. I really love the crust I get on my corn bread made this way. I also used 2 cups of raspberries simply because I had them. My entire family really enjoyed this cake. We will certainly be making it again. As a funny side note we had two brothers visiting us today. They thought I had fed them poison they disliked it so much. It was their first time tasting cornmeal...didn't go over well. We loved it!

