Rating: 3
These were super quick & yummy. My favorite raspberry muffins are from a bakery nearby and they have a little almond taste to them, so I added 1/4 t. almond extract to my batch. It was a perfect addition and I highly recommend it. Next time I make them, I'll try to make them in advance and pop them into the fridge for a little while/overnight before baking them. It makes most corn muffins puff up beautifully.

Rating: 2
The bonus for this recipe is that it is rather foolproof. I accidentally left them in the oven an extra 10 minutes, and they came out just fine! Unfortunately, the end product just doesn't pack a lot of punch. Perhaps the texture of the raspberries and the texture of the corn meal is just too much grit. For the record, I used 1/4 cup yogurt and 1 cup sour cream, as that's what I had on hand, and baked using muffin cups, which may explain why these babies didn't burn!

